		<div class="quote"><p>@Martijn: It's not that it's unusable. It's that you're asking people who may not be familiar with your particular region to perform tasks. They might not have enough context to understand what works and what doesn't. Hence why I try to edge them in the right direction by providing resources that are more likely to yield better results. </p>
<p>Is a language barrier going to make it more difficult? I don't know but I certainly expect it might complicate things.</p>
<p>The service is definitely marketed to Americans but I've had success with it, even though I'm in Canada.
